20/05/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The interior ministers of Bulgaria, Romania and Serbia signed a joint declaration Tuesday (May 19th) on mechanisms against cross-border organised crime, terrorism and corruption. 
Meeting in the northern Bulgarian town of Vidin, Bulgaria's Mihail Mikov, Romania's Dan Nika, and Serbia's Ivica Dacic discussed ways to further expand police and customs co-operation through the establishment of a joint contact centre in Bulgaria. 
It will facilitate exchanges of information on border control and illegal immigration. 
The joint declaration underscored the three countries' roles in guaranteeing regional security and stability. 
(BNR, Sofia news agency, News.bg - 19/05/09)
